verses.rendering:
The former things I declared long ago;
they went out from my mouth and I announced them.
Then suddenly I acted, and they came to pass.

They are created now, not long ago;
before today you have not heard of them,
lest you say, 'I already knew that.'

You have neither heard nor known;
from of old your ear has not been opened.
For I knew you would act utterly treacherously;
you have been called a rebel from the womb.

For the sake of my name I defer my anger;
for the sake of my praise I hold it back from you,
so as not to cut you off.

I, even I, have spoken;
indeed I have called him.
I have brought him, and he will succeed.
